actions, such as grasping or reaching, are outcomes of representing features of the environment in relation to features and skills of the acting subject. The author discusses the hierarchical development from egocentric, context-specific action-related representations to abstract representations of general actions. Findings from Philosophy, Neuroscience and Ecological Psychology are analysed, and a novel approach to the understanding of Gibson's Theory of Affordance Perception, a key element of the concept of action-related representation, is introduced.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by CRC 991: The Structure of Representations in Language, Cognition, and Science  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 4aEmbodied Cognition. 4aGrounded Cognition. 4aRepresentationalism. 4aTheory of Perception. 4aVisuomotor Pragmatic Processing. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / General.2bisacsh  aAbstract Cognition.  aAction.  aAffordances.  aEmbodied Cognition.  aGrounded Cognition.  aTheory of Perception.  aVisuomotor Pragmatic Processing.2 aCRC 991: The Structure of Representations in Language, Cognition, and Scienceefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z97831